Pick an ID format for the job, then import only that generator."},"273":{"id":"/docs-1","page_id":"/docs","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs#the-library-contract","content":"The library contract"},"274":{"id":"/docs-2","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs","content":"Install uniku once, then choose the identifier that fits the boundary in front of you: a database index, a public URL, or an API payload. Every generator has its own entry point, so a UUID, ULID, TypeID, Nanoid, CUID v2, KSUID, ObjectID, XID, or TSID only adds the strategy your application imports."},"275":{"id":"/docs-3","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs","content":"<Card title=\"Install uniku\" href=\"/docs/getting-started\" description=\"Generate your first ID in one import.\" icon=\"<PackageOpen />\" />"},"276":{"id":"/docs-4","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs","content":"<Card title=\"Choose an ID\" href=\"/docs/guides/choosing-an-id\" description=\"Compare formats by the job they need to do.\" icon=\"<ScanLine />\" />"},"277":{"id":"/docs-5","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs","content":"<Card title=\"Use the CLI\" href=\"/docs/cli\" description=\"Generate, inspect, and validate without writing a script.\" icon=\"<Terminal />\" />"},"278":{"id":"/docs-6","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs","content":"<Card title=\"Migrate to uniku\" href=\"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries\" description=\"Move from a familiar ID package without changing stored identifiers.\" icon=\"<ArrowRightLeft />\" />"},"279":{"id":"/docs-7","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#the-library-contract","content":"The library is ESM-only, built on web standards, and tested end to end across Node.js, Bun, Deno, browsers, and Cloudflare Workers. Its supported `1.x` entry points, validation boundaries, and runtime support policy are defined in the stability contract."},"280":{"id":"/docs-8","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#the-library-contract","content":"Install @uniku/cli when you need an ID in a terminal, migration, or shell pipeline. It shares the library's formats but has its own release lifecycle."},"281":{"id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries","page_id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries","type":"page","content":"Migrate from other libraries","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Migration"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries"},"282":{"id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries-0","page_id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries","content":"Keep familiar formats while moving to direct, portable imports."},"283":{"id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries-1","page_id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries#from-uuid","content":"From `uuid`"},"284":{"id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries-2","page_id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries#from-nanoid","content":"From `nanoid`"},"285":{"id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries-3","page_id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries#from-ulid","content":"From `ulid`"},"286":{"id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries-4","page_id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries#from-typeid-js","content":"From `typeid-js`"},"287":{"id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries-5","page_id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries#from-paralleldrivecuid2","content":"From `@paralleldrive/cuid2`"},"288":{"id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries-6","page_id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries#from-owpzksuid","content":"From `@owpz/ksuid`"},"289":{"id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries-7","page_id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries#from-bson","content":"From `bson`"},"290":{"id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries-8","page_id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries#from-tsid-ts","content":"From `tsid-ts`"},"291":{"id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries-9","page_id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries#from-xid-ts-or-nexid","content":"From `xid-ts` or `nexid`"},"292":{"id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries-10","page_id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries","content":"Migration is usually an import change first. Keep the stored identifier format stable, then move generation behind the new direct entry point. Every example below shows the value returned by the uniku generator."},"293":{"id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries-11","page_id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries#from-uuid","content":"uniku only generates UUID v4 and v7. There is no uniku equivalent for v1, v3, v5, or v6; keep the `uuid` package for those, or generate them elsewhere and only use uniku for v4 and v7 values."},"294":{"id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries-12","page_id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries#from-uuid","content":"The rest of `uuid`'s API maps onto uniku's per-generator methods, scoped to the version you imported:"},"295":{"id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries-13","page_id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries#from-uuid","content":"`uuid`"},"296":{"id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries-14","page_id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries#from-uuid","content":"uniku"},"297":{"id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries-15","page_id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries#from-uuid","content":"`parse(id)`"},"298":{"id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries-16","page_id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries#from-uuid","content":"`uuidv4.toBytes(id)` / `uuidv7.toBytes(id)`"},"299":{"id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries-17","page_id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries#from-uuid","content":"`stringify(bytes)`"},"300":{"id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries-18","page_id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries#from-uuid","content":"`uuidv4.fromBytes(bytes)` / `uuidv7.fromBytes(bytes)`"},"301":{"id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries-19","page_id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries#from-uuid","content":"`validate(id)`"},"302":{"id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries-20","page_id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries#from-uuid","content":"`uuidv4.isValid(id)` / `uuidv7.isValid(id)`"},"303":{"id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries-21","page_id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries#from-uuid","content":"`version(id)`"},"304":{"id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries-22","page_id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries#from-uuid","content":"Implied by which `isValid` matches: `uuidv4.isValid` accepts only version 4, `uuidv7.isValid` accepts only version 7."},"305":{"id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries-23","page_id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries#from-typeid-js","content":"`typeid-js` returns a TypeID object. uniku returns the canonical string directly."},"306":{"id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries-24","page_id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries#from-tsid-ts","content":"`tsid-ts` exposes a TSID object. uniku uses the native `bigint` as TSID's primary value."},"307":{"id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries-25","page_id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries#from-tsid-ts","content":"Convert at a string boundary when you need the canonical Base32 form:"},"308":{"id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries-26","page_id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries#from-xid-ts-or-nexid","content":"Both libraries implement the rs/xid representation. uniku returns the canonical string directly and does not require asynchronous setup."},"309":{"id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries-27","page_id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries#from-xid-ts-or-nexid","content":"Use `xid.toBytes(id)` and `xid.fromBytes(bytes)` when you store the 12-byte value."},"310":{"id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries-28","page_id":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/migration/from-other-libraries#from-xid-ts-or-nexid","content":"Before replacing an existing generator, test the representation you store and expose. UUIDs, ULIDs, ObjectIDs, and XIDs have canonical byte forms; Nanoid and CUID v2 are string-native."},"311":{"id":"/docs/migration/v1","page_id":"/docs/migration/v1","type":"page","content":"Migrate to uniku v1","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Migration"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/migration/v1"},"312":{"id":"/docs/migration/v1-0","page_id":"/docs/migration/v1","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/migration/v1","content":"Prepare for the v1 entry-point contract without changing identifier data."},"313":{"id":"/docs/migration/v1-1","page_id":"/docs/migration/v1","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/migration/v1#move-cuid-v2-to-the-versioned-entry-point","content":"Move CUID v2 to the versioned entry point"},"314":{"id":"/docs/migration/v1-2","page_id":"/docs/migration/v1","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/migration/v1#what-remains-stable","content":"What remains stable"},"315":{"id":"/docs/migration/v1-3","page_id":"/docs/migration/v1","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/migration/v1","content":"uniku v1 keeps its public generator entry points stable and removes one pre-v1 compatibility alias."},"316":{"id":"/docs/migration/v1-4","page_id":"/docs/migration/v1","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/migration/v1#move-cuid-v2-to-the-versioned-entry-point","content":"`uniku/cuid2` is a pre-v1 alias. Use the canonical versioned import before upgrading:"},"317":{"id":"/docs/migration/v1-5","page_id":"/docs/migration/v1","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/migration/v1#move-cuid-v2-to-the-versioned-entry-point","content":"The generator behavior is the same. This is an import migration, not a data migration: existing CUID v2 values remain valid."},"318":{"id":"/docs/migration/v1-6","page_id":"/docs/migration/v1","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/migration/v1#what-remains-stable","content":"Within `1.x`, uniku will not remove or rename documented entry points, exports, options, methods, or constants. Canonical string formats, byte order, timestamp units, and documented error codes are part of the contract."},"319":{"id":"/docs/migration/v1-7","page_id":"/docs/migration/v1","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/migration/v1#what-remains-stable","content":"Read the stability contract for the full release and runtime policy."},"320":{"id":"/docs/reference/cuid-v2","page_id":"/docs/reference/cuid-v2","type":"page","content":"CUID v2","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Reference"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/reference/cuid-v2"},"321":{"id":"/docs/reference/cuid-v2-0","page_id":"/docs/reference/cuid-v2","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/reference/cuid-v2","content":"Non-sequential, string-native identifiers that resist enumeration."},"322":{"id":"/docs/reference/cuid-v2-1","page_id":"/docs/reference/cuid-v2","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/reference/cuid-v2","content":"CUID v2 is for public values where predictability is the problem. It is string-native, so there is no byte codec to maintain or expose."},"323":{"id":"/docs/reference/entry-points","page_id":"/docs/reference/entry-points","type":"page","content":"Entry points","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Reference"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/reference/entry-points"},"324":{"id":"/docs/reference/entry-points-0","page_id":"/docs/reference/entry-points","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/reference/entry-points","content":"The stable direct imports exposed by uniku."},"325":{"id":"/docs/reference/entry-points-1","page_id":"/docs/reference/entry-points","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/reference/entry-points#generator-references","content":"Generator references"},"326":{"id":"/docs/reference/entry-points-2","page_id":"/docs/reference/entry-points","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/reference/entry-points","content":"The package root is intentionally not exported. Import a generator or metadata module directly:"},"327":{"id":"/docs/reference/entry-points-3","page_id":"/docs/reference/entry-points","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/reference/entry-points","content":"Two metadata entry points round out the library:"},"328":{"id":"/docs/reference/entry-points-4","page_id":"/docs/reference/entry-points","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/reference/entry-points","content":"Import"},"329":{"id":"/do